            <p><strong><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2016/12/06/technology/samsung-apple-smartphone-patent-supreme-court.html" target="_blank">Justices Hand Samsung a Victory in Patent Fight with Apple</a></strong></p>
            <p>In a relatively favorable ruling for Samsung, the U.S. Supreme court determined that the smartphone giant may not have to turn over the full $399 million in profits that Apple was previously awarded in the patent infringement lawsuit it brought against Samsung for allegedly copying the iPhone’s design. The opinion did not resolve the case, but instead drew a distinction between cases in which the article of manufacture from which profits are derived consists of a finished product, as opposed to those involving only components of that product. The Court did not answer the question of which category this case falls into, but instead sent it back down to the Federal Circuit Court to determine the appropriate amount of damages.</p>
