            <p><strong><a href="http://blogs.wsj.com/law/2016/12/09/court-wife-may-not-use-facebook-to-notify-husband-of-divorce/" target="_blank">Court: Wife May Not Use Facebook to Notify Husband of Divorce</a></strong></p>
            <p>A court in Brooklyn has ruled that a woman cannot use Facebook as the sole means of serving her husband with a divorce summons. The woman argued that she could not find another way to communicate with her husband, who she believes was deported and is living in Saudi Arabia. However, the judge was not comfortable relying exclusively on social media, especially given that the husband’s Facebook page did not appear to have been updated since 2014, and it can be difficult to prove the authenticity of a social media account. This decision represents a growing trend among judges of denying parties’ requests to effect service through Facebook.</p>
