            <p><strong><a href="http://www.siliconbeat.com/2016/12/08/yahoo-data-breach-class-action-suits-joined-together-in-san-jose-federal-court/" target="_blank">Yahoo Data-Breach Class Action Lawsuits Joined Together in San Jose Federal Court</a></strong></p>
            <p>A panel of federal judges in San Jose, California combined 5 of at least 23 lawsuits that have been filed against Yahoo following its disclosure of a 2014 hack that compromised the data of an estimated 500 million users. The judges indicated that because these cases raise common issues of fact, and the company is located in their Bay Area district, making evidence more easily accessible there, centralizing the actions within the San Jose federal court served the convenience of the parties and witnesses.</p>
