            <p><strong><a href="http://www.latimes.com/business/technology/la-fi-tn-yahoo-shares-verizon-20161216-story.html" target="_blank">Yahoo’s Latest Data Breach Could Mean An Even Bigger Price Cut For Verizon</a></strong></p>
            <p>Yahoo’s recent admission of an August 2013 hack that involved more than 1 billion user accounts could derail or significantly hinder the proposed deal for Verizon’s purchase of the embattled tech company. This latest data breach, which appears to be unconnected to a previously disclosed 2014 breach affecting over 500 million users, is believed to be the largest in history. Analysts predict that Verizon, which expressed interest in a price reduction after the first breach disclosure, may now demand an even deeper discount, assuming the deal remains in tact. The transaction was originally slated to close in the first quarter of 2017.</p>
