            <p><strong><a href="http://www.siliconbeat.com/2016/12/06/google-to-be-100-green-powered-by-end-of-2017/" target="_blank">Google to be ‘100% Green-Powered’ by End of 2017</a></strong></p>
            <p>Google has announced that its offices and data centers all over the world will be powered by renewable energy by the end of the year. The tech giant stated that it is the largest corporate buyer of green energy worldwide, purchasing more than many large utilities. Google’s commitment to renewable energy is significant given that data centers have become one of the fastest-growing energy consumers in recent years. The company will still need to pull power off the conventional grid at times, but will offset these cases by investing in renewable energy entities that create green power surpluses.</p>
