            <p><strong><a href="http://www.abajournal.com/news/article/law_firm_is_ordered_to_pay_nearly_27k_for_suit_over_bad_online_reviews" target="_blank">Law Firm is Ordered to Pay Nearly $27K for Suit Over Bad Online Reviews</a></strong></p>
            <p>A court in Texas has thrown out a law firm’s claim against its former client and sanctioned it to the tune of almost $27,000 in attorney fees for bringing the lawsuit. The firm’s libel case was dismissed under state anti-SLAPP laws. The former client had posted on Yelp and Facebook that the firm’s lawyers were “super unprofessional” and “pushy” after they allegedly came to her home and into her bedroom in order to obtain her business following a car accident. The firm filed suit after she refused to take the posts down in response to their cease and desist letter.</p>
