            <p><strong><a href="http://money.cnn.com/2016/12/21/technology/uber-california-dmv/" target="_blank">Uber Stops California Self-Driving Car Program After DMV Puts the Brakes On</a></strong></p>
            <p>Following some controversial back-and-forth with the DMV, and the subsequent threat of an injunction from the state Attorney General, Uber has ceased operating the 16 self-driving cars it recently deployed in San Francisco. Uber had previously maintained that it did not need the permits the DMV is requiring on the basis that the cars at issue don’t meet the agency’s definition of autonomous vehicles. However, several of Uber’s competitors have cooperated with the DMV before testing self-driving cars on public roads. The DMV ultimately revoked the Uber vehicles’ registrations until the permitting process is complete.</p>
